column13: Control is channel and appears clear.
column14: Moving boat measurement (SP w/ARC boat #128) ~10m U/S of gauge. Measurement files were misnamed (09AE006_20211010). Root folder and summary PDFs have been corrected. Transects from LB to RB exhibit odd velocities at the top of the water column. The ARC boat and transducer were inspected for anything out of the ordinary but nothing was seen. Wind? Air entrainment? This is a brand new transducer with no previous measurements. A filter was applied in QREV to exclude these velocities (WT Filter: exclude distance below 0.1m). Navigation Reference: BT (BT: 22.6, GGA: 22.6, VTG: 22.6). Uncertainty - COV: 0.99%. Uncertainty - Total: 3.9%. No QREV messages. No QA/QC concerns. Medium confidence measurement.  DWL at metal bar.  No discernible HWM.  Depth of sensor at 12:00: DWL(3.973) - Offset(2.464) = 1.509m.  ADCP by Moving Boat
